          "date": "2017-03-16 11:21:48.000000000",
          "tz": 330
        },
        "subject": "LU-0000 mgs: remove skip records from config file",
        "message": "LU-0000 mgs: remove skip records from config file\n\nThis is debug patch for only_mgs_is_running()\nverification.\n\nConfiguration logs are append-only files of limited size.\nOver the course of time the logs may grow over the limit size.\nUsually, configuration logs keep needless records marked\nas SKIP. The new lctl command \"clear_conf\" is added to\nallow administartors to clear configuration files by\nremoving mentioned SKIP records. lctl man page is updated.\nconf-sanity test is added to test the new command.\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly testlist=conf-sanity\nSigned-off-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@seagate.com>\nChange-Id: Ia8195bd9423598f2a8b80fedc511997078b75418\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
